text.section: The parties to a document having a delayed effective date, time, or both may withdraw the filing before it takes effect.
To withdraw a document, the parties shall deliver a statement of withdrawal to the Secretary of State for filing.

A statement of withdrawal shall:
Be signed on behalf of each party to the action or transaction contemplated by the initial document in accordance with KRS 14A.2-020;
State the nature of the document to be withdrawn, the date of the filing, and the parties to the filing; and
State that the document has been withdrawn in accordance with the agreement of the parties.
From the filing by the Secretary of State of a statement of withdrawal, the action or transaction evidenced by the original filing shall not take effect.
A statement of withdrawal shall be accompanied by a filing fee equal to that of the filed document that is being withdrawn.

law.history: Created 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 151, sec. 15, effective January 1, 2011.
